	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The "real" problem is you keep blowing into your games. It's bad STOP IT. The contacts both in the nes and on the game corrode thanks to this making them not work again. I found that usually "reseating" games in a certain way would make them work. With a new connector sometimes the games even work better if they are in "up" position.

		

		</td>
